[
    {
        "content": "<p>Say I have some type <code>G</code> and a <code>Group G</code>. Does Mathlib provide a Prop-valued way of saying \"this subset of <code>G</code> is actually a subgroup\"? Or should one simply build a <code>Subgroup G</code> structure?</p>\n<p>(I would like to have a theorem statement of the form, \"under such and such assumption on a subset <code>A</code>, this <code>A</code>is actually a subgroup\", with the statement mentioning <code>A</code>; if I just build a subgroup structure, I might as well be building a trivial subgroup unrelated to <code>A</code>)</p>",
        "id": 515075758,
        "sender_full_name": "Philippe Duchon",
        "timestamp": 1745936066
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>One way to express it:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">example</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">G</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Type</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">_</span><span class=\"o\">}</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">Group</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">G</span><span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">A</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Set</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">G</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"bp\">âˆƒ</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">H</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Subgroup</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">G</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">A</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">H</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"gr\">sorry</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 515077578,
        "sender_full_name": "Kyle Miller",
        "timestamp": 1745936512
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>A more indirect way:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">example</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">G</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Type</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">_</span><span class=\"o\">}</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">Group</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">G</span><span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">A</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Set</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">G</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">Subgroup</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">closure</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">A</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">A</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"gr\">sorry</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
